    "body": "### Problem\n\nMy left alt key produces ISO_Level3_Shift, which activates a new keyboard layer when pressed.\r\n\r\nIn Neovim, holding down the left alt key activates the layer for a brief moment immediately after the key is pressed. If no key is pressed within that small window of time, the layer deactivates, and pressing any key afterward produces a character as if the left alt key wasn't pressed.\r\n\r\nHowever, if a key is pressed during that brief period, the layer remains active for as long as the left alt key is held.\r\n\r\nThe same behavior occurs with ISO_Level5_Shift.\r\n\r\nIn other applications, such as the terminal or browser, holding down the left alt key keeps the layer active, regardless of whether any keys are pressed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nmap ISO_Level3_Shift to left alt and try to use that layer inside neovim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nkeyboard layer should work for as long as the key that activates it is being hold regardless of any key being pressed or not.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.18.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nsystem package manager",
